'''Ken Bone''' is the head men's basketball coach at [[Portland State University]].  He was selected as the 2007-08 [[Big Sky Conference]] Men’s Basketball Coach of the Year after taking the Vikings to their first ever [[2008_NCAA_Men's_Division_I_Basketball_Tournament|NCAA Tournament]]. Previously, Bone coached [[Seattle Pacific University]] for 13 years, compiling a 251-97 (.721) record and making 8 appearances in the [[NCAA Men's Division II Basketball Championship|NCAA Division II Tournament]], reaching the semifinals in 2000.
